cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MM

This paper discusses the use of energy harvesting in cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization and control of network resources, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the statistical analysis of energy arrival and traffic load, which could be related to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper mentions the use of renewable energy in mobile networks, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
